ing?\tNo\tOfficial FlexiFunnels response Can you copy HTML via browser inspect?\tTechnically yes, but broken\tSee below WHY \"VIEW SOURCE\" WON'T WORK Even if you tried to manually copy HTML from a FlexiFunnels page: Issue\tProblem\tResult in GHL Dynamic JavaScript\tFF pages rely on proprietary JS for interactivity\tBroken buttons, forms, timers CDN-hosted assets\tImages, fonts, CSS hosted on FF servers\tMissing assets, broken styling Cloudflare dependencies\tEdge optimization, lazy loading\tPage won't render correctly CRO elements\tTimers, social proof, exit popups\tNon-functional Checkout integration\tFF checkout is server-side\tCan't replicate Bottom line: You'd get a broken, non-functional shell — not a working page. YOUR REAL OPTIONS Option 1: Keep FF for Sales Pages (RECOMMENDED) Copy GHL Blog → Link to → FF Sales Page → FF Checkout → Webhook → GHL Delivery Why this works: FF handles what it's best at (CRO, fast pages, checkout) GHL handles what it's best at (blog, SEO, CRM, email, courses) 1% checkout fee is the cost of conversion optimization Option 2: Use FF as Design Reference, Rebuild in GHL Step\tAction\tTime\tQuality Loss 1\tAI-generate page in FF\t7 min\t— 2\tScreenshot each section\t5 min\t— 3\tManually rebuild in GHL drag-drop\t2-4 hrs\t~30% CRO loss 4\tRe-add copy manually\t30 min\t— 5\tRecreate timers/proof (if GHL supports)\t30 min\tLimited options Result: 3-5 hours per page, inferior CRO, but 0% checkout fee Option 3: Hybrid Fee Minimization Use FF for landing pages only, route to ThriveCart or GHL checkout: Copy GHL Blog → FF Landing Page (no checkout) → CTA Button → GHL/ThriveCart Checkout Component\tPlatform\tFee Landing page\tFlexiFunnels\t$0 (no transaction) Checkout\tThriveCart (you own)\t0% Delivery\tGHL\t$0 Caveat: You lose FF's checkout CRO features (bump offers, one-click upsells on FF checkout). DECISION MATRIX Scenario\tBest Path\tMonthly Fee on $10K Revenue Maximum conversions\tFF full funnel (Option 1)\t$100 (1%) Zero fees priority\tRebuild in GHL (Option 2)\t$0 Balanced approach\tFF landing → ThriveCart checkout (Option 3)\t$0 MY RECOMMENDATION For your 50-offer business at scale: Revenue Level\tRecommendation\tRationale < $5K/mo\tOption 3 (FF landing → ThriveCart)\tMinimize fees while building $5K-$20K/mo\tOption 1 (FF full funnel)\t1% fee worth the CRO lift > $20K/mo\tOption 1 + A/B test Option 3\tTest if ThriveCart checkout converts equally The conversion lift from FF's CRO (timers, social proof, exit intent, bump offers) typically generates 15-30% more revenue — far exceeding the 1% fee. KNOWLEDGE BASE UPDATE Doc ID\tTitle\tStatus KB-008\tFlexiFunnels HTML Export Limitations\tNEW KB-008a\tFF → GHL Page Migration Options\tNEW Want me to map out: Option 3 architecture (FF landing → ThriveCart checkout → GHL delivery) with full webhook setup? A/B test plan to compare FF checkout vs ThriveCart checkout conversion rates? GHL page rebuild checklist if you want to try manual recreation for specific pages? Skill plate, seems to be good for creating the course or creating the deliverable. and, Flexifunnels is better for the sales generation and the front-end landing page and funnel setup. How would I merge those to best practices? Or is there another platform that is better? I could try to use the format that flexifunnels create and then just use cloth. For, creating my landing pages. Let me research the current state of Skillplate's course creation features and compare integration options. Using Tool | Search Skillplate course creation features LMS 2026 AppSumo View Using Tool | Search Skillplate webhook integration external checkout Stripe View Using Tool | Search Claude AI landing page builder website generator View Using Tool | Search Skillplate external checkout bypass commission ThriveCart integration View Using Tool | Search FlexiFunnels Skillplate integration webhook course enrollment View Using Tool | Read https://skillplate.com/integrations View Using Tool | Search Skillplate API webhook incoming student enrollment external View Using Tool | Search GoHighLevel course membership vs Skillplate comparison View Using Tool | Read https://appsumo.com/products/skillplate/questions/?page=16 View Using Tool | Search Skillplate Zapier integration enroll student external purchase webhook View Using Tool | Search \"Claude artifacts\" HTML landing page export host website View Using Tool | Read https://appsumo.com/products/skillplate/questions/some-questions-1433170/ View Using Tool | Search Skillplate AppSumo webhook trigger enrollment manually add students API View Now I have a complete picture. Let me give you the definitive answer on merging Skillplate with FlexiFunnels, plus the Claude alternative you mentioned. FLEXIFUNNELS + SKILLPLATE: THE HYBRID ARCHITECTURE You've identified the right specialization: Platform\tBest At\tUse For FlexiFunnels\tSales pages, CRO, funnels, AI page builder\tFront-end conversion Skillplate\tCourse creation, AI content, LMS, community\tProduct delivery GHL (you own)\tCRM, email, automation, blog/SEO\tBackend operations INTEGRATION VIABILITY CHECK Skillplate Integration Capabilities (Confirmed) Feature\tStatus\tSource Webhooks (outgoing)\t✅ Yes\tTriggers when student registers/enrolls/buys Webhooks (incoming)\t✅ Yes\tCan receive external triggers API for adding students\t✅ Yes\tVia Activepieces/webhooks (still in testing) Manually add students\t✅ Yes\tAdmin can add without payment Zapier-style integrations\t✅ Yes\t180+ apps via built-in Activepieces External checkout bypass\t⚠️ Possible\tBut they advise against it The Commission Reality Checkout Source\tSkillplate Fee\tNotes Skillplate native checkout\t10% (Tier 2) or 1% (with addon)\tStandard External checkout (FF/ThriveCart)\t0% to Skillplate\tBut may lose some features 0% Commission Addon\t~$99-199 one-time\tEliminates ongoing fee RECOMMENDED HYBRID STACK ARCHITECTURE Copy ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │                         TRAFFIC SOURCES                              │ │              (SEO/AEO Blog, Ads, Social, Email)                      │ └────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ ▼ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │                    GOHIGHLEVEL (yourbrand.com)                       │ │  • Blog/SEO/AEO content                                              │ │  • Email marketing & CRM                                             │ │  • Lead capture forms                                                │ │  • Automation workflows                                              │ └────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ CTA Links ▼ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │              FLEXIFUNNELS (offers.yourbrand.com)                     │ │  • AI-generated sales pages (8 credits for masters)                  │ │  • Advanced CRO (timers, social proof, exit intent)                  │ │  • Checkout with bump offers (1% fee)                                │ │  • Upsell/Downsell sequences                                         │ └────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ Webhook (purchase complete) ▼ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │           SKILLPLATE (learn.yourbrand.com or courses.brand.com)      │ │  • AI-generated course content                                       │ │  • Video hosting (30 hrs Tier 2)                                     │ │  • Student portal & progress tracking                                │ │  • Community features                                                │ │  • Certificates & quizzes                                            │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ WEBHOOK INTEGRATION FLOW (FF → SKILLPLATE) Step-by-Step Data Flow Step\tTrigger\tAction\tPlatform 1\tCustomer clicks \"Buy Now\"\tLands on FF checkout\tFlexiFunnels 2\tCustomer completes purchase\tFF processes payment (1%)\tFlexiFunnels 3\tPurchase complete\tFF fires webhook with customer data\tFlexiFunnels → Pabbly/Zapier 4\tWebhook received\tCreate/update user in Skillplate\tPabbly/Zapier → Skillplate 5\tStudent enrolled\tGrant course access automatically\tSkillplate 6\tConfirmation\tSend welcome email + login details\tGHL or Skillplate Webhook Payload (FF → Skillplate via Pabbly) Copy Email: customer@email.com Name: John Doe Product: Course XYZ Transaction ID: FF-12345 Amount: $97 FEE COMPARISON: HYBRID VS ALL-IN-ONE Option A: FlexiFunnels Checkout → Skillplate Delivery Component\tFee\tOn $10K Revenue FlexiFunnels checkout\t1%\t$100 Skil"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=6eb53e9f-092a-4677-a7a4-aad66a465d52","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=6eb53e9f-092a-4677-a7a4-aad66a465d52"}]}]}]
